# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Olhar de Tutor — Environment variables reference
# Copy to .env.local and fill in real values.
# Never commit .env.local — it is in .gitignore.
#
# TWO separate env scopes exist:
#   1. VITE_*  — baked into the browser bundle at build time (this file)
#   2. Edge Function secrets — set separately, see supabase/functions/.env.example
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ─── Supabase (required) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Project Settings → API → Project URL
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=

# Project Settings → API → anon (public) key
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# DO NOT add the service_role key here. It is injected automatically into
# supabase/functions/ by Supabase. See docs/SECURITY.md §6.

# ─── Push notifications / Web Push VAPID (optional) ──────────────────────────
# The PUBLIC key is safe to embed in the browser bundle.
# The PRIVATE key must NEVER go here — set it as a Supabase Edge Function secret.
#
# Generate a key pair once:
#   npx web-push generate-vapid-keys
#
# Then:
#   • paste the public key below
#   • paste the private key in supabase/functions/.env.example → VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY
#   • set both in the Vercel dashboard AND in Supabase secrets
#
# Leave empty to disable push notifications without breaking anything.
VITE_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY=

# ─── Vercel dashboard variables (NOT in .env.local) ──────────────────────────
# These are server-side values consumed by the Vercel cron API routes in
# api/notifications/. Set them in the Vercel project dashboard:
#   Settings → Environment Variables
# They are NOT prefixed with VITE_ and must NOT go in .env.local.
#
# NOTIFICATION_SECRET=<random string>  # auth token between Vercel cron → Supabase Edge Function
#                                      # same value must be set as a Supabase secret too
#
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL is reused at the Vercel serverless function level;
# Vercel makes all dashboard env vars available to API routes via process.env.
